# Version Context

This project is **v0 pre-release**. There are zero users in production and zero legacy serialized data.

## Serialization

- `formatVersion` is `1`. This is the first and only format version.
- On deserialization, missing `formatVersion` is accepted for backward compatibility. When present, only `1` is accepted; any other value throws.
- Do NOT introduce migration layers, backwards-compatibility shims, or format version upgrade paths beyond the existing missing-version tolerance.

## Constraints

- Do NOT add code to handle "legacy" data formats beyond what already exists.
- Do NOT introduce version bumps or format migrations until the project reaches v1 with real users.
- When v1 ships, migration infrastructure can be introduced. Until then, keep the serialization path simple and direct.
